                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17364347" author="luguangming" created="Wed, 16 Jun 2021 15:31:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The TConfiguration passed down can be used when the TmemoryInputTransport member is initialized in TSASLTransport,&#160;This allows you to specify a TConfiguration when constructing TTransport, avoiding a fixed 100MB write-down&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17364486" author="jensg" created="Wed, 16 Jun 2021 19:22:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wonder why source code has to be in a picture these days.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17364625" author="luguangming" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2021 01:35:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;merge links&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://example.com/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/commit/3ccef5cecd131077782038cf2be3a6a471c467c5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17364626" author="luguangming" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2021 01:39:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jensg&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Jens Geyer.&lt;/a&gt;&#160;thrift-0.13 is normal and should have been introduced in 0.14&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17365126" author="jensg" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2021 20:29:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have no idea what you mean by &quot;is normal&quot;. The most current stable release is 0.14.2 (since right now) and the next one will most certainly be a 0.15.0, targeted to be ready in (circa) late summer this year. This is also the version that contains the patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But since this is open source, you are absolutely free to use the current development version from the repository, or any other customized build based on any branch you wish. Normal or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
